        "title": "feat: add editable voice dictation to the Control UI",
        "body": "Closes #98026\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nOpenClaw's Control UI offers realtime Talk, but users cannot dictate an ordinary editable chat draft. They must rely on inconsistent OS-level dictation or start a conversational realtime session that can invoke an agent instead of simply returning text.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis adds a composer-native, independently written batch-dictation workflow: click the microphone or hold `Ctrl+M`, record with waveform/timer feedback, cancel or confirm, then review the transcript inserted at the captured selection before sending. The browser uses standard media APIs and the Gateway delegates to the existing `tools.media.audio` provider/CLI pipeline, so there is no second credential, model, or fallback stack.\n\nThe additive `audio.transcribe` method requires `operator.write`, accepts supported base64 audio up to 12 MB, writes only a private temporary file for path-based local transcribers, and removes it after every attempt. Browser recordings remain memory-only and stop after two minutes.\n\nAlternatives rejected in the included ADR: browser Web Speech (inconsistent vendor/provider control), a dictation-only STT stack (duplicated policy), and realtime Talk (different product semantics).\n\n## User Impact\n\nControl UI users can dictate prompts, see live recording feedback, cancel safely, recover from permission/device/provider errors, and edit the transcript before sending. The workflow works with existing cloud STT providers or local Whisper CLI configuration. Setup, privacy controls, observable Cursor UX research, supported-browser notes, and the ADR are documented in `docs/web/dictation.md`.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/chat/dictation-recorder.test.ts` — 5 passed\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts -t \"chat composer dictation\"` — 2 passed\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/server-methods/audio.test.ts` — 4 passed across Gateway projects\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/methods/registry.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods-list.test.ts` — 32 passed\n- Product TypeScript lane (`tsconfig.core.json`) — passed\n- UI test TypeScript lane (`test/tsconfig/tsconfig.test.ui.json`) — passed\n- `pnpm ui:i18n:check` — all 20 locales clean\n- `node scripts/build-all.mjs gatewayWatch` — passed, including lazy Gateway packaging/import guard\n- `pnpm ui:build` — passed (932 modules)\n- `node scripts/check-docs-mdx.mjs docs/web/dictation.md docs/web/control-ui.md` — passed\n- `node scripts/docs-link-audit.mjs` — 5,496 links checked, 0 broken\n- Live isolated Windows loopback smoke test — Control UI loaded the new accessible Dictate control and correctly rendered actionable microphone-permission denial/recovery UI. Recording/waveform, shortcut, cancellation, insertion, and cleanup are covered with injected browser/media tests; physical microphone runs on macOS/Linux remain for CI/reviewer device validation.\n- The preferred remote `check:changed` lane could not start because the local Blacksmith Testbox binary failed its own sanity check. A broad source-test TypeScript lane also timed out without diagnostics; the touched production and UI-test lanes passed.\n- Full `pnpm build` exceeded the local timeout during its broad declaration phase; the relevant Gateway watch package build and production Control UI build both passed afterward.\n\nThis PR is AI-assisted. The implementation and tests were reviewed locally, and no proprietary Cursor code, assets, protocols, or confidential behavior were used. No transcript log is attached because it contains local workspace context; the durable research/design/validation summary is included in the docs and this PR body.\r\n",
